# QCanvas Project Intelligence (.cursorrules)

## Read This First
- Always read ALL Memory Bank files at the start of each task.
- Treat `docs/project-scope.md` as the authoritative scope and exclusions.
- Keep Memory Bank and rules aligned with scope; remove anything out-of-scope.

## Scope Anchors
- Frameworks: Qiskit, Cirq, PennyLane
- IR: OpenQASM 3.0 (focus on Iteration I; Iteration II planned)
- UI: Next.js Web IDE with visualization and results
- Backend: FastAPI REST + WebSocket, OpenQASM conversion, simulation API

## Explicit Exclusions
- Pulse/OpenPulse, calibration, waveforms, frames, ports
- Circuit timing (delay, duration literals, box)
- Hardware-specific extensions and extern functions
- Memory management and quantum error correction

## Architecture Patterns
- Hybrid architecture (Next.js + FastAPI); WebSocket for long ops
- Shared TypeScript types; Pydantic models align with frontend interfaces
- Converter pattern (parsers → QASM generator → converters)
- Strategy pattern for simulation backends

## Development Workflow
- Use todos for multi-step tasks; one active in_progress at a time
- Update todos after each successful step
- Prefer editing existing files; keep diffs minimal and readable
- Maintain type hints (Python) and TypeScript types across services

## Documentation Discipline
- Update `memory-bank/activeContext.md` after significant changes
- Keep `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md` in sync with actual architecture
- Record progress in `memory-bank/progress.md` at milestones

## Testing & Quality
- Write tests for new functionality (unit/integration/e2e as appropriate)
- Enforce linting and type checks (PEP 8, ESLint/TS)
- Prioritize clear, educational code and error messages

## Links
- Project Scope: `docs/project-scope.md`
- System Patterns: `memory-bank/systemPatterns.md`
- Active Context: `memory-bank/activeContext.md`
